Antennae with 10 segments. Body elongated, slightly dorso-ventrally flattened, in apical part slightly widened, brown, antennae and legs slightly brighter than body (
Fig. 1
). Pronotum narrower than elytra. Elytra with larger punctures arranged in more or less regular rows, intervals flat, sparsely and irregularly punctured, punctures smaller. Surface between punctures microreticulate. Body dorsally with conspicuous pubescence of two types . Pubescence of main type with hairs short, cling and dense that punctuation of dorsal part almost invisible. Secondary pubescence with hairs long, bright, spaced. Hairs leaning posteriad.
